m the Denver\nmint to the First National and Stock\nGrowers' National banka, Cheyenne,\nto partially cover paymenta made by\nthese banks from their government\ndeposits to Fort Russell contractors\nand workmen for October conetrnction\nwork.\nWAS A POOR ADVERTISEMENT.\nRgld-Headod Barber Could Not Be*\nBottle of Hair Restorer.\nIt was In a barber shop near tho\n\u2022rand Central station. There wee a\nman In one of the chain getting n\nahavo and the srtlet In charge was\nperforming the operation leisurely\nand silently. It wns not until the last\nvestige of hirsute obstrueUoa had eno.\nnumbed to the taxor's edge, and the\npatient's face had been copped, wiped,\nwtteh haceled and powdered that the\nbarber deigned to open hia lipa. Then,\nrunning hie Sngera through the hair\non the top of the men's bead, remark\ned Innocently:\n\"Hair la getting thin. Got just the\nthing for It Olorln Hair Restorer.\nBtlmulates the roots of tbe hair. War\nranted to make hair, grow on a bil\nliard ball. Fifty cents a boule!\"\nHaving delivered blmself of thin,\nbe plnced a bottle In tbe hands of tbe\nman In the chair for inspection. The\nman glanced at toe bottle sad then at\nthe bead of tbe barber, which was ae\nbald as tbe aforementioned billiard\nbait and asked\n\"This must be what you oaadF'\u2014\nNew York Prune\nJob Printing\u2014\nJ~lfW Until we can pro\nvide away to do it\nat Torrington, me\na /1 U will have it done at\nthe best equipped\n'CEF? printing office on\nu 7 the river\u2014by A. B.\n_____ Wood at Garing.\nRAAA Your orders are so-\nllcited. Prices will\nabsolu.cly not be advanced, and\nyou'll get the best produc.ions.\nThe Telegram\nW.G- CURTIS\nU. S. COMMISSIONER\nCareful attention to any busmens that\nmay come before me.\nOffice hours\u20149am to 12m, 1 to 6pm.\nTorrington Wyoming\nJ. L. SAWYER\nATTORNEY AT LAW\nReal Estate Insurance\nNotary Public Collections\nTorrington Wyoming\nH. PLATZ, M. D.\nPHYSICIAN AND SURGEON\nDiseases of Women\nTorrington Wyoming\nT'G.powhs\nREAL ESTATE AND LIVE STOCK\nI buy and sell anything in the line ol\nreal estate and live stock. If you want\nbargains, call, write or Phone No. 17\nTorrington Wyoming\nfJ.V, REEVES\nTHE ONLY PAINTER, PAPER\nHANGER AND DECdKATOR.\nAll work guaranteed. Telephone on\nPlatte Valley line.\nAthol Wyoming\nW a H. CADLE\nCONTRACTOR>ND BUILDER\nEstimate, furnished upon application.\nTorrington WyooKw\nQMAS. AKERBLADE j\nBLACKSMITH AND WooDWorAr\nHorace hoeing a afwcialty and penLl\nrepair work promptly dons g\nTorrington u vn| ^L\nxee* Strata Abea\u00df.\nPay no attention to slander or gossip\nmongers. Keep straight on in your\ncourse, and let their backbitings die the\ndeath of neglect What is the use of\nlying awake brooding over the remarks\nof some false friend that run through\nyour brain like forked lightning? What'\ns the use of getting into a worry and\nfret over gossip that haa been set afloat\nto your disadvantage by aom j meddle\nsome bueybody, who has more time\nthan character? Those thinge can't\npossibly injure you, unless indeed, you\ntske notice of them and in combating\nthem give them character and etanding\nIf what is said about you is true, set\nyourself right at once; if it is false, let\nit go for what ft will fetch. If a bee\nstings you, would you go to the hive\nand destroy it? Would not a thousand\ncome upon you? It is wisdom to aay\nlittle respecting the injuries you have\nreceived. We arc generally losers in j\nthe end if we stop to refute all the\nbackbitinga and goeaipinga we may\nhear by the way. They are annoying,\nit Is true, but not ..angerous so long u\nwe do not stop to expostulate and scold\nOur characters are formed and sustsin\ned by ourselves and by our own actions\nand purpos<\u00ab, and by others. Let us\nalways bear in mind that calumniators\nmay usually be trusted to time ar.d tl.e\nslow out steady justice of public\nopinion. 6Ko\u00bb.\nDon't forget the children's Thanks\ngiving service Sunday evening.\nTm\u00dfey SBeot.\nAn old time tnrkey shoot will be\ngiven at Fretwell\u2019s Billiard Hall in\nTorrington, Tuesday Nov. 26, 1907, at\n10, o'clock A. M. Everybody come.\nWwCR LOWb WmSUJm\u00ab\nAny one having good young milch\ncowa to sell can find sale for them by\naddroesing Lock Box 14, Torrington.\nWyoming.\nYbOMk\u00dftfW\u00dfg DaBM.\nA Thanksgiving Dance will be\ngiven In Emory\u2019s Hall Friday even\ning November 29, 1907. Good music\nand a good time assured everyone.\nBy order of Committee.\nGtva nb aN year lab w*rk. While\ntor Wvo present Ura work Is to be\nBom at Galas. rcaraaOar not aw\npricas wBl not be a\u00dfvaaee\u00df.\nTba\u00dfkaaMnt Paaeg.\nA big dance will be given at tbe\nfamous Fort Laramie resort, Wednes\nday evening November 27, 1907. A\ngood time is promised to every one.\nDon't forget the date.\nJOE WILDE, Prop.\nUva PeOar\u00df Pewar\u00df\nFive dollars reward will be paid for\ninformation leading to the arrest and\nconviction of any parties shooting at\ninaulatoni on telephone or telegraph\nlines.\nPLATTE VALLEY TELEPHONE CO.\nNattca la Teacbars.\nNotice is hereby given that an ex\namination for teachers' certificates will\nbe held in Cheyenne on the Friday\nand Saturday following Thanksgiving,\nvia: November 29th and 30th, 1907.\nThis is to take the place of the ususl\nDecember examination. None will be\ngiven m December this year on account\nof tho State Teachers, aaaociatlun\nmeeting at that time.\nThose desiring to take the exami\nnation are requested to meet at the\ncourt house not later than 9 a. m.\nupon the dateo given above.\nALICE M. SAMPSON,\n6w 11 28. County Superintendent\nHMRH Torrta\u00dftoo, Wyo.\nI'\u00bbu> East 2:2opm\nW'\u00abl 1243 pm\nFn-ight. East 10,20.. m\n\u25a0\u25a0\u25a0\u25a0U Freight, Went 2:9opm\nS. C. CLARKE, Agent\nllmmru StotM mmi momm*\nLufek^Ma' Patrick-Graves .Yuee\nThurs and Sat. 7:ooam. Arrivee Mon.,\nWed. and Fri. 6:oopm.\nEMPIRE-Leave Mon. and Fri. 2:30\npm. Arrive Mon. and Fri. I:2opm.\nE. L. BONNELL. P. M.\nai^^mm^Ma'\n